			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Adhesive (Solid Hot Melt)</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">胶粘剂（固体热熔）</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">HOT MELT ADHESIVE; Hot glue,胶粘剂（固体热熔）</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">HOT MELT ADHESIVE; Hot glue,胶粘剂（固体热熔）</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Organic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Hot-melt adhesives are well suited for rapid assemblies, typically using a glue gun. The adhesive is melted, applied, and allowed to cool. The hot formula wets the surface when applied and, upon cooling, hardens to make the glue joint. HMAs are thermoplastic and do not change when heated. They can be remelted and used again. These adhesives are made using a thermoplastic polymer as the base material. They are melted so that they can be coated in liquid form before hardening back into a solid form as they cool.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">热熔胶非常适合快速组装，通常使用胶枪。粘合剂熔化、涂抹并冷却。涂抹时，热配方会润湿表面，冷却后会变硬，形成胶接。HMA 是热塑性塑料，加热后不会发生变化。它们可以重新熔化并再次使用。这些粘合剂使用热塑性聚合物作为基材。熔化后，它们可以液态形式涂覆，然后在冷却后变回固态。</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
